p: Thirty four (8%) of the laboratory confirmed IV had been vaccinated. Vaccine effectiveness (VE) to prevent infection against laboratory confirmed IV in primary care setting was 14% (95%CI: 0, 47); stratifying by type of IV the VE was 69% (95%CI: 31, 88) for IVA and 2% (95%CI: 0.69, 5.62) for IVB.
